The West African country, exported 69.3 tons of gold last year, compared to 63.9 tons in 2021, according to statistics seen by Reuters. The metal contributes to around a quarter of the country's fiscal resources. The value of last year's exports was around 2 001 billion CFA francs ($3.24 billion), compared with around 1,867 billion CFA francs ($3.02 billion) the previous year. Mali is one of Africa's top gold producers and home to industrial mines operated by companies including Barrick Gold , B2Gold Corp, Resolute Mining, AngloGold Ashanti, and Hummingbird Resources. It exports mainly to South Africa, followed by Switzerland and Australia. Industrial gold production was around 4.4% higher in 2022 than the previous year because of improved performance in the sector. But it is forecast to fall this year. Gold reserves stood at around 881.7 tons in October, Finance Minister Alousseni Sanou said on Thursday.  --Reuters--